# All of these are injected by `neon dev` and written by `neon env pull`
# (from the `neon.ts` policy + your linked branch). You normally don't edit them by hand.
#
# Just run:
#   neon link
#   neon deploy   # provisions services and writes .env.local for you
#
# The variables Neon will populate:
#
#   NEON_BRANCH                    The linked branch name (e.g. "main").
#
#   # Postgres
#   DATABASE_URL                   Pooled connection string for the branch.
#   DATABASE_URL_UNPOOLED          Direct (non-pooled) connection string.
#
#   # Object storage (preview.buckets in neon.ts) — picked up by the AWS S3 SDK
#   AWS_ACCESS_KEY_ID              S3 access key (a Neon credential token id).
#   AWS_SECRET_ACCESS_KEY          S3 secret access key.
#   AWS_ENDPOINT_URL_S3            Branch S3 endpoint host.
#   AWS_REGION                     us-east-2 (the only preview region).
#
#   # AI Gateway (preview.aiGateway in neon.ts) — picked up by the OpenAI SDK / AI SDK
#   OPENAI_API_KEY                 Gateway bearer token (a Neon credential).
#   OPENAI_BASE_URL                Full OpenAI Responses route on the gateway.
#   NEON_AI_GATEWAY_TOKEN          Same bearer (kept under a Neon-branded name).
#   NEON_AI_GATEWAY_BASE_URL       Bare gateway host (no path).
#
# See https://neon.com/docs/compute/functions/environment-variables for the full reference.
